            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.21.21_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                
                <opener>A Wonderful Speaker</opener>
                <p>The speaker at assembly this morning was a most unusual and interesting man. He seemed to be intensely interested in every thing that went on about him. He was a small man physically. He was short in stature untill<sic>until</sic> he started to speak. Then it seemed as tho<sic>though</sic> he magicly<sic>magically</sic> became tall. You thought of him as a large, <hi rend="underline">dynamic</hi> person. His voice was wonderful and seemed to carry <del/><add>you</add> along with him. I saw Black Eagle sitting and smoking and thinking silently. Then he spoke, <add>and</add> told me of his youth and how he was happy to know and talk to one who was interested in and cared for the Indians. It was as tho<sic>though</sic> I traveled with them to Harvey Peak in the Black Hills. I saw Black Eagle on his last journey to the scene of his youthful vision, all thru<sic>through</sic> the power of Mr. Neihardt's voice. I heard Black Eagle speaking to the six great powers of the world. He begged forgiveness for his sins of omission in the distant past. The sky above the mountain became overcast, and rain began to fall. Black Eagle lifted up his face and cried out for pity and mercy.</p>
                
